<task id="033" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>P2-CLOSEOUT-02 Surface ChatSession.UploadedFiles[] in PlaybookChatContextProvider so the chat agent sees uploaded files</title>
    <status>🔲</status>
    <status-note>Closeout task added 2026-06-04. Without this, even after 032 populates UploadedFiles[], the chat agent's tool-call reasoning doesn't know files exist (verbatim agent response on Dev: "I don't see the document uploaded yet"). See notes/summarize-vertical-remediation-plan.md §3.2.</status-note>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration (CLOSEOUT)</phase>
    <wave>P2-G9-CLOSEOUT (parallel-safe with 032; both must complete + deploy before 034)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>004 (ChatSession.UploadedFiles model), 011 (Summarize playbook with PlaybookCapabilities.Summarize), 015 (InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool registered behind that capability gate)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff-api, chat, context-provider, integration, closeout, sev-1-fix</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Update the chat-agent context provider chain so the agent's tool-call
    reasoning has a clear signal that uploaded files exist in the current
    session. Without this signal, the LLM correctly declines to invoke
    InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool because — from its view of context — no files
    are present.

    The InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool (R5 task 015) is registered in
    SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools at line ~856 inside the
    `capabilities.Contains(PlaybookCapabilities.Summarize)` gate. The gate
    passes for the `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` playbook (deployed via
    task 011). So the tool IS registered. The agent simply doesn't invoke it
    because it has no awareness of session files.

    Modify:

    1. `ChatContext.cs` model — add an additive nullable field
       `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;? UploadedFiles = null` (backward
       compatible with all existing consumers; null = no change in behavior).

    2. `PlaybookChatContextProvider.GetContextAsync` (file
       src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs)
       — read `session.UploadedFiles` and forward it on the returned
       `ChatContext`. Three sites to update (one per branch — see lines ~77
       "no playbook" path, ~118 "standalone host context" path, and the main
       playbook-resolved path at the end of GetContextAsync).

    3. `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` (or wherever the system prompt
       gets composed from ChatContext) — when
       `context.UploadedFiles is { Count: > 0 }`, append a SHORT system-prompt
       suffix like: `"\n\nSession Files: This chat session has {N} uploaded
       file(s) available for tool calls: {comma-separated fileNames}. When
       the user asks to summarize, invoke the `invoke_summarize_playbook`
       tool with these file IDs: {comma-separated fileIds}."`

       Keep wording compact (token budget). Do NOT include file content or
       chunk text in the prompt — only the manifest (fileId + fileName).

    4. Verify ChatContextMappingService (if it exists) — when used, also
       propagate UploadedFiles through.

    Update or add unit tests:

    - PlaybookChatContextProvider_GetContextAsync_SurfacesUploadedFiles_WhenSessionHasFiles
    - PlaybookChatContextProvider_GetContextAsync_LeavesUploadedFilesNull_WhenSessionHasNone
    - SprkChatAgentFactory_AppendsSessionFilesNoteToSystemPrompt_WhenUploadedFilesPresent
    - SprkChatAgentFactory_DoesNotAppendNote_WhenUploadedFilesEmpty
    - Round-trip: ChatSession with 2 UploadedFiles → context → factory →
      tool invocation receives both fileIds in the InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool
      argument when the LLM mock chooses to call (verify via captured args)

    NOTE: this task does NOT auto-trigger Summarize after upload (that's
    task 034). This only ensures the agent SEES the files when reasoning
    about whether to call the tool in response to user intent.

    Acceptance: with this task deployed (alongside 032), when a user uploads
    a file and then types "summarize" or "/summarize" in chat, the agent's
    system prompt includes the file manifest, and the LLM invokes
    InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool with the correct fileIds.
  </prompt>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatContext.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs</file>
